It's all fan-canon that sort of misses the whole point of the original mythos.
The thing about wendigos in the original Algonquin myth is, they're humans that turn against the most fundamental taboos of their people and fall into a cursed cycle. All the ways they're described is in relation to a human being distorted, there's nothing about them becoming animalistic or bestial. The whole idea is that they turn into the most monstrous type of humanity possible, like a ghoul, not that they become something feral or fundamentally different from humanity, it's the worst of humanity intensified into a monstrous form. So creating an anthro wendigo full of animal traits is the exact opposite of what the moral really is, about the terrible natures lurking in our own species specifically.
